# Scaffold generators

When adding **new** files that match the kinds below, run **`pnpm scaffold`** instead of writing empty components, hooks, stores, enums, constants, layouts, types, mocks, utilities, or tests from memory.

## Command

```bash
pnpm scaffold --list-kinds
pnpm scaffold <kind> <name> [--base <path-from-repo-root>] [--dry-run] [--force]
```

Kinds: `component`, `constant`, `enum`, `hook`, `layout`, `mock`, `store`, `style`, `test`, `type`, `utility`.

Defaults and examples: **`.cursor/scaffold/README.md`**. Human-oriented templates: **`.cursor/templates/README.md`**.

## After scaffolding

1. Wire real imports, DTOs, and props; replace placeholders (`PLACEHOLDER`, `string[]`, etc.).
2. Run post-action verification (**`@code-standard.mdc`**).

## Related

- **`@code-standard.mdc`** — barrel rule, BEM, hook naming, verification.
- **`@component-patterns.mdc`** — tests and snapshots.
